{
  "root_cause": "With SGLANG_USE_IPC_POOL_HANDLE_CACHE disabled, concurrent multimodal requests use per-feature CUDA/HIP IPC storage handles. The sender-side feature allocation can be released and recycled before a TP scheduler opens that handle, so the receiver attempts to reconstruct a stale device pointer.",
  "fix": "Set SGLANG_USE_IPC_POOL_HANDLE_CACHE=1 in launch_qwen3.5_27b_sglang.sh while retaining SGLANG_USE_CUDA_IPC_TRANSPORT=1. This makes receivers reuse an opened handle to the long-lived multimodal IPC memory pool instead of opening a short-lived per-feature allocation handle.",
  "evidence": "crash_qwen3.5-27b-mmmu-con128.log lines 3614-3647 show TP1: 'Failed to deserialize from CUDA IPC handle (HIP error: invalid device pointer)' followed by reconstruct_on_target_device at cuda_ipc_transport_utils.py:488 and torch.AcceleratorError: HIP error: invalid device pointer. Line 763 also records the multimodal MmItemMemoryPool under load."
}
